    class ValueQueue
extends java.util.concurrent.LinkedBlockingQueue<SimpleData>
    This is a blocking queue, with a split-iterator, that blocks until the next element is put into the queue. The split-iterator signals an end of input data, if
    • a dummy-SimpleData is found in the queue. This is done, when the DataPoint is released or
    • when the thread, which is executing the stream is interrupted. In this case the interrupt- flag is not reset!
